To POV-PBS,<br><br>
This has been a great site for many. The one thing dialog does is confront the emotions of those participating and not just sitting in the background. I for one have come to ackowledge the views of some against our involvement in Vietnam. I have fought and argued with a few. I have also come to defend those views I don't agree with.<br><br>
Yet the most amazing thing is I have seen a couple that initially were attacking us vets because we chose not to break the laws of the land, to a position of understanding and acceptance.<br><br>
This can only happen when people are given the chance to speak their piece without having to worry about someone pulling a gun, knife, bat, or any number of weapons.<br><br>
I would hope you can find the funds to keep the site going even if you have to trim it down some. Maybe you can clean up the unused threads into an read-only archive.<br><br>
I am a Vietnam Vet struggling to survive and make a living. This site has opened my mind and heart to the people with all viewpoints.<br><br>
Thanks PBS.
